import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['normal', 'actual']])
    plt.title("What is the distribution of normal and actual temperatures?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Normal', 'Actual'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='forecast', data=data, label='Forecasted Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual Temperature')
    plt.title('How does the forecasted temperature compare to the actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='forecast', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['forecast'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['forecast'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of forecasted temperatures?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Forecasted Temperatures")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
